# FastAPI Rules (extends 00-core.mdc)

## Layer Separation
- Routes: thin — validate via Pydantic schema → call service → return response model. No business logic.
- Services: pure business logic. No DB imports, no HTTP imports.
- Repositories: data access only. Behind interfaces for testability.

## Dependency Injection
- Use `Depends()` for auth, DB sessions, config, rate limiting.
- Config via `pydantic-settings` in `core/config.py`.

## Async
- `async def` for I/O-bound work (DB, HTTP, files).
- Do NOT wrap CPU-heavy work in async. Use `run_in_executor` or task queue.

## Quality
- Run `ruff check . && ruff format --check . && mypy app tests && pytest` after changes.
- All route functions return explicit Pydantic response models — no untyped dicts.
- Use code review checklist in `AGENTS.md` §7 before submitting.


